issue.title: Earnings by Category estimate bug
issue.body: On the Earnings by Category report, the "Monthly Sales Avg" and "Monthly Earnings Avg" columns it seems to be basing the estimate for the entire month based on the estimate through that day in the month. For example, on a site that makes $3000 a month, instead of an estimated earnings of $3000, on the 2nd day of the month it would show $200. Same for sales

issue.title: BonMot disables IBActions dragging from storyboard
issue.body:
When Bonmot is included in my project, all my UIButton 'Touch Up Inside' events in the connections inspector via Utilities show warning signs. I suspect it has something with this stack overflow issue: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/28732903/cant-connect-ibaction-in-xcode.

![screen shot 2016-11-26 at 12 21 13 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10264891/20642041/3672b6ae-b3d3-11e6-947d-553eaa527c3e.jpg)


As one of the commenters suggested in the link, the culprit seems to be the UIButton extensions in BonMot's framework.

I commented the several extensions for UIButton out and now it works fine.

Going to work with clone bonmot into own project in meantime, but would love for this to be addressed!

comment.body: Sorry again for the delay. If you've been seeing this problem, please try the fix from https://github.com/Raizlabs/BonMot/pull/259 and let us know if it works for you. We should be able to get it merged pretty soon.

issue.title: #73: Fixed an issue such that when binding a model fails, the response still gets printed.
issue.body:
Related issue: #73.

I changed the `call()` method so that it keeps the raw response received which is then sent to the events, in case of failure. This will allow the Response Printer to print the response even when we don't have a `ModelResponse`.
